<p>Dear {!Contact.FirstName},</p>
<p><b><u>IAVA's mission is more important now than ever.</u></b> The first quarter of the year has been one where IAVA's work has been at the forefront and we are making an impact.</p>
<p>This year IAVA promoted <a href="https://iava.org/people/12413/">Melissa Bryant</a> to IAVA Chief Policy Officer. She has hit the ground running on IAVA's policy position, including pushing IAVA's landmark legislation directly tied to <a href="https://iava.org/she-who-borne-the-battle/">#SheWhoBornetheBattle, our campaign to recognize and support women veterans</a>. This year alone we have added over a dozen new sponsors signed on to our signature legislation, the Deborah Sampson Act.</p>
<p>Over the past few days IAVA has been helping share our communities view of the dismissal of Secretary Shulkin from the VA and the impending nomination of replacements. <a href="http://iava.org/press-release/post-911-veterans-react-to-firing-of-va-secretary-shulkin/">Here is IAVA's official position</a> on the sudden, but not unexpected news. If you haven't been able to see the videos and hear the radio spots over the past couple days, I have linked them below.</p>
