<p><b><u>Additional milestones of first quarter of the year:</u></b>
<ul>
  <li>IAVA ensured that government shutdowns didn't negatively impact veterans. Here is a link to a blog post explaining why the <a href="http://iava.org/blogs/shutdown-update-where-are-we-and-whats-next/">shutdown matters for veterans</a> written by Melissa.</li>
  <li>IAVA is fighting for our members. Our new <a href="http://iava.org/big6/">Big 6 policy agenda</a> was introduced and you can check it out here. two new topics click <a href="http://iava.org/campaign/initiate-support-for-injuries-from-burn-pits-toxic-exposure/">here (Burn Pits)</a> and <a href="http://iava.org/campaign/initiate-empowerment-of-veterans-who-want-to-utilize-cannabis/">here (Cannabis)</a>. And you can see <a href="http://iava.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/IAVA_Policy_2017_v8_125bleed.pdf">last years' comprehensive Policy Agenda here</a>.</li>
  <li>Melissa joined with the VA office to discuss empowering veterans through technology... <a href="https://www.facebook.com/8607847994/videos/10157127012707995/">click here to view the program in its entirety</a>.</li>
  <li>Over the past quarter IAVA generated over 28 million impressions through our social media and traditional media. IAVA is uniquely able to reach the masses.</li>
  <li>IAVA's best in class research department helps us create and distribute polls to influence popular opinion to ensure that our members voices are heard through the tumult and chaos that enveloped the rest of Washington. We polled out membership on the need or desire for a <a href="http://iava.org/press-release/post-911-veterans-sound-off-on-military-parade/">Military Parade in Washington</a> and a <a href="http://iava.org/press-release/post-911-veterans-sound-off-on-va-leadership-shulkin/">review of Dr. Shulkin</a>. The largest comprehensive non-government survey of Post 9/11 veterans, IAVA's member survey will be launching soon.</li>
